his philosophy of nonviolence...

233
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:58,269
...I bet he didn't know how much fun
it was killing stuff.

234
00:12:59,079 --> 00:13:02,310
All right, I think we got them all.
Let's divide up the loot.

235
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,710
BERNADETTE: Ooh, look at this
pretty purple robe I just got.

236
00:13:04,879 --> 00:13:07,074
You should put on yours
and then we'll match.

237
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:09,800
But I worked hard to get this armor, heh.

238
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:13,748
Sorry, ljust thought it'd be nice
if people knew we were a couple.

239
00:13:14,759 --> 00:13:16,078
Fine, I'll change.

240
00:13:17,799 --> 00:13:19,630
[WHIP CRACKS ON PHONE]

241
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:24,909
[CACKLES]

242
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,872
I don't think I wanna play a game.

243
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,600
They're playing one across the hall.
We should too.

244
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:37,309
Okay, we are gonna take turns
bouncing a quarter off the table.

245
00:13:37,479 --> 00:13:40,039
If it goes into this cup,
the other person has to drink.

246
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:42,919
Then you get to go again, and you ki--

247
00:13:46,319 --> 00:13:49,470
-Like that?
-Wow, yeah, beginner's luck.

248
00:13:49,639 --> 00:13:52,199
So now I will drink this entire cup of beer...

249
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:55,238
...and you will go again and we can--

250
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:01,632
All right, so, yeah.
Okay, now I'm gonna drink this entire cup.

251
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:03,790
And then I'm going to drink another one.

252
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:06,748
Okay, seriously, stop. What the hell?

253
00:14:07,719 --> 00:14:11,189
I spent my childhood throwing coins
into wishing wells hoping for friends.

254
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:14,796
At a certain point, you start doing
trick shots to keep things interesting.

255
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,315
Oh, give me a second
to catch up here, hold on.

256
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:19,311
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY
THROUGH WALL]

257
00:14:19,999 --> 00:14:21,352
That'd be my boyfriend...

258
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:25,030
...happier playing his Star Trek game
with friends than hanging out with me.

259
00:14:25,199 --> 00:14:27,235
-Wars.
-What?

260
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:30,280
Star Wars. They get all cranky
when you mix the two up.

261
00:14:30,719 --> 00:14:34,428
-What's the difference?
-There's absolutely no difference.

262
00:14:36,439 --> 00:14:38,589
How do I get him to treat me better?

263
00:14:38,959 --> 00:14:41,837
All right, let me give you
a little Girlfriend 101.

264
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,830
Usually the first move is you withhold sex...

265
00:14:44,999 --> 00:14:47,559
...but that will work better
after Sheldon hits puberty.

266
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:52,870
So I'd say give him the silent treatment.

267
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:55,396
-No, he loves that.
-Hmm.

268
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:58,313
Our record for sitting in a room together
and not speaking...

269
00:14:58,519 --> 00:15:01,989
...is six and a half hours.
He said it was a magical evening.

270
00:15:02,399 --> 00:15:05,118
All right, we're gonna have
to go with an oldie but goodie:

271
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:08,510
-Making a scene.
-I don't think I'd be good at that.

272
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:10,591
Ah. You're lucky to have me.
Back in Omaha...

273
00:15:10,759 --> 00:15:13,990
...there are two restaurants
I'm not allowed into. Both Chili's.

274
00:15:17,519 --> 00:15:20,352
Bernadette, your character
is the healer in our group.

275
00:15:20,519 --> 00:15:22,874
In charge of healing all of us,
notjust Howard.

276
00:15:23,039 --> 00:15:27,112
Can't help it.
My Howie-Wowie has an owie. Ha, ha.

277
00:15:28,959 --> 00:15:32,838
That is the most sickeningly sweet thing
I have ever experienced.

278
00:15:32,999 --> 00:15:36,628
And lam sipping Kool-Aid
through a Red Vine.

279
00:15:39,079 --> 00:15:43,072
Sheldon, I've got a bone to pick with you,
and I'll do it in front of all your friends.

280
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,959
Yeah, you pick that bone.
You pick that bone clean.

281
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,830
I'm gonna publicly shame you
and then sit back...

282
00:15:48,999 --> 00:15:51,559
...as societal pressure compels you
to modify your behavior.

283
00:15:51,719 --> 00:15:53,835
Oh, burn!

284
00:15:55,159 --> 00:15:57,798
If you don't start treating me better,
I'm leaving you...

285
00:15:57,959 --> 00:16:00,075
...for a miniature-horse breeder
named Armin.

286
00:16:02,079 --> 00:16:04,468
-Armin who?
-Armin-- Damn it.

287
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:11,554
Sheldon, she wanted to show you off to
her family and you stood her up, okay?

288
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:14,076
I mean, look at this adorable,
smushy face.

289
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:17,118
Smush, smush, smush.

290
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:21,632
-You're hurting me.
-No, Sheldon hurt you.

291
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:24,234
-Before. Now it's you.
-Oh.

292
00:16:25,759 --> 00:16:27,715
I think I understand.

293
00:16:28,199 --> 00:16:31,714
You're the one person who can say
Sheldon Cooper is your boyfriend.

294
00:16:31,879 --> 00:16:35,554
But that rings hollow if you can't
lord him over others in the flesh.

295
00:16:37,319 --> 00:16:41,631
I forget what I bring to the party
and what I take away when I leave.

296
00:16:42,199 --> 00:16:47,114
Please accept these valuable
Cooper Coupons...

297
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:51,519
-...as restitution.
-She doesn't want your stupid coupons--

298
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,911
The Science Center? Redeeming. Let's go.

299
00:16:56,680 --> 00:17:00,559
Well played, Amy Farrah Fowler.
Let me get my coat.

300
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,709
[WHIP CRACKS ON PHONE]

301
00:17:01,879 --> 00:17:03,358
Oh, grow up, Leonard.

302
00:17:04,959 --> 00:17:07,154
Excuse me, I have something to say.

303
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:12,799
None of you may realize it, but I was very
much looking forward to this weekend.

304
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,392
It was gonna be like the old days.
The four of us hanging out...

305
00:17:16,559 --> 00:17:19,517
...playing video games,
before you guys all got girlfriends.

306
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:24,029
Do you have any idea what it's like
to be the only one without a girlfriend?

307
00:17:24,199 --> 00:17:25,473
Even if I get one someday...

308
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:29,599
...l'll still be the guy who got a girl
after Sheldon Cooper!

309
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:37,477
And that's how a girl makes a scene.

310
00:17:41,799 --> 00:17:44,074
I'm sorry. You're right.
You deserve your weekend.

311
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:46,800
-Come on, Amy, let's go.
-What about the Science Center?

312
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,798
Oh, I'll let you hold my hair
while I throw up.

313
00:17:51,239 --> 00:17:52,513
Rain check.

314
00:17:53,919 --> 00:17:56,194
-l'm gonna go too.
-l'll miss you.

315
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:58,396
-l'll miss you.
-But I'll miss you more.

316
00:17:58,559 --> 00:18:00,515
-No, I'll miss you--
-Just leave.

317
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:07,269
Ahh. Okay, now,
this is the way it's supposed to be.

318
00:18:07,439 --> 00:18:09,475
Men together, fighting the forces of evil.

319
00:18:09,919 --> 00:18:11,477
HOWARD: All right.
-Hear, hear.

320
00:18:12,439 --> 00:18:13,792
Ah.

321
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:16,076
Can't believe this is only 64 calories.

322
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,559
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

323
00:18:28,719 --> 00:18:31,870
MRS. WOLOWITZ: Howard Joel Wolowitz,
I've been worried sick for two days...

324
00:18:32,039 --> 00:18:34,269
...and I know you turned off your phone!

325
00:18:36,919 --> 00:18:40,195
You open up this door right now,
because I've had it up to here!

326
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:42,430
l have been to the morgue
and the hospital...

327
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:46,838
...and I've spent the last half-hour
walking up these farkakte stairs!

328
00:18:49,839 --> 00:18:52,114
That's my ride. Gotta go, heh.

329
00:18:54,279 --> 00:18:55,871
[WHIP CRACKS ON PHONE]

330
00:19:22,719 --> 00:19:24,710
